request.description:
Update an existing batch. All fields are optional. However, if you provide nested objects (scheduled, duration, capacity, age, fee_structure), you must provide ALL required fields within those objects.

Example - Simple update (only top-level fields):
{
  "name": "Updated Batch Name",
  "status": "published"
}

Example - Complete update with nested objects:
{
  "name": "Updated Morning Batch",
  "scheduled": {
    "start_date": "2024-12-01",
    "start_time": "09:00",
    "end_time": "11:00",
    "training_days": ["monday", "wednesday", "friday"]
  },
  "duration": {
    "count": 3,
    "type": "month"
  },
  "capacity": {
    "min": 10,
    "max": 30
  },
  "age": {
    "min": 8,
    "max": 12
  },
  "fee_structure": {
    "fee_type": "monthly",
    "fee_configuration": {
      "base_price": 2000
    }
  },
  "status": "published"
}

Requires batch:update permission.

